<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669765>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Egg capsules of Scyliorhinus species. A, S. canicula, AMNH 4121 (Naples, Italy); B, S. capensis, SAIAB 6286 (Algoa Bay, South Africa); C, S. retifer, AMNH 15611 (United States). Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669765/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669751>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Neotype of Scyliorhinus canicula (Linnaeus, 1758), NHMUK 1866.9.10.4, male, 417.1 mm TL (Nice, France). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669751/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669753>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Scyliorhinus canicula; dorsal view. A, NRM 50450, female, 468.6 mm TL (Skagerrak, Sweden); B, MNHN 1999–1732, female, 418.5 mm TL (Roscoff Station, France, 48°53’1.2”N, 3°58’58.8”W); C, ZMH 100467, female, 411.9 mm TL (North Sea, 52°56’N, 2°50’E); D, USNM 221602, female, 258 mm TL (Western Morocco, 35°09’N, 6°32.20’W). Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669753/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669755>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Scyliorhinus canicula. A, C, NRM 50183, male, 582.4 mm TL (Southern Bohüslan, Sweden); B, D, E, F, MNHN 1999–1732, female, 418.5 mm TL (Roscoff Station, France, 48°53’1.2”N, 3°58’58.8”W); G, NHMUK 1983.8.3.1–4, male, 585.7 mm TL (Dale Roads, Pembrokeshire, United Kingdom). A, B, ventral view of head; C, detail of pectoral fins; D, lateral view of head; E, dorsal view of head; F, detail of pelvic fins and claspers. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669755/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669757>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Teeth of Scyliorhinus canicula; labial view. NHMUK 1970.12.2.1–4, female, 413.6 mm TL (Malaga Bay, Spain). a, anterior tooth; c, commissural; l, lateral; ps, parassymphysial. Scale bar = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669757/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669759>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Dermal denticles of Scyliorhinus canicula. A–C, NHMUK 1970.12.2.1–4, female, 413.6 mm TL (Malaga Bay, Spain); D–F, NHMUK 1983.8.3.1–4, male, 585.7 mm TL (Dale Roads, Pembrokeshire, United Kingdom). A, D, region above pectoral fin base; B, E, region below first dorsal fin origin; C, F, region below second dorsal fin insertion. Scale bar = 250 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669759/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669761>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Clasper of Scyliorhinus canicula; dorsal view, NHMUK 1983.8.3.1–4, 585.7 mm TL (Dale Roads, Pembrokeshire, United Kingdom). A, external morphology; B, skeleton. crh, cover rhipidion; end, endstyle; erh, exorhipidion; hp, hipopyle; rd, dorsal marginal cartilage; rv, ventral marginal cartilage; td, dorsal terminal cartilage; t3, terminal 3 cartilage; td2, dorsal terminal 2 cartilage; tdc, terminal dermal cover; tv, ventral terminal cartilage; tv2, ventral terminal 2 cartilage. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669761/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669763>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Map showing the geographic distribution of Scyliorhinus canicula based on material examined in this study. Black star indicates the neotype locality." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669763/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669747>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Clasper skeleton of Scyliorhinus species distributed along the southwestern Atlantic; dorsal view of skeleton. A, Scyliorhinus cabofriensis, UERJ 1702, 468 mm TL; B, S. haeckelii, UERJ 2233.6, 449 mm TL; C, S. ugoi, UERJ 1725, 530 mm TL. end, endstyle; rd, dorsal marginal cartilage; rh, rhipidion; rv, ventral marginal cartilage; td, dorsal terminal cartilage; td2, dorsal terminal 2 cartilage; tv, ventral terminal cartilage; tv2, ventral terminal 2 cartilage. Modified from Soares et al. (2015, 2016). Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669747/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

